OL,3,COverstretched NHS putting cancer
OL,4,Cpatients at risk, ombudsman warns
OL,6,FOnly 64.1% of patients started
OL,7,Ftreatment within 62 days of cancer
OL,8,Fbeing suspected, meaning nearly
OL,9,F100,000 waited longer than they should.
OL,11,FThe waits have worsened every year for
OL,12,Fthe past 11.
OL,14,FMr Behrens called for "concerted and
OL,15,Fsustained action from Government to
OL,16,Fmake sure NHS leaders can prioritise
OL,17,Fthe safety of patients and are
OL,18,Faccountable for doing so".
